
/**
 * \page install_yarp_on_ubuntu Install YARP (Ubuntu)

We use YARP for communications. Installing YARP on Ubuntu is quite straightforward. Note that you will be prompted for your password upon using '''sudo''' a couple of times:

\verbatim
sudo apt-get install build-essential libace-dev subversion
sudo apt-get install libgsl0-dev  # Needed for creating YARP lib_math we use for kinematics
sudo apt-get install libgtkmm-2.4-dev  # Needed for YARP GUIs: yarpview, gyarpmanager
sudo apt-get install libjpeg8-dev   # Needed for mjpeg_carrier for ravebot cam on web
svn co https://yarp0.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/yarp0/trunk/yarp2
cd yarp2; mkdir build; cd build
cmake .. -DCREATE_LIB_MATH=ON -DCREATE_GUIS=ON -DCREATE_OPTIONAL_CARRIERS=ON -DENABLE_yarpcar_mjpeg_carrier=ON
make -j3;  sudo make install; cd ../..
\endverbatim

For additional options use ccmake instead of cmake.

Do not forget to set the YARP_ROOT environment variable to ''yarp2'' and the YARP_DIR environment variable to ''yarp2/build''. There are two ways of doing this:

 1) Through ~/.profile (parsed on reboot). For this option, type:
 
\verbatim
echo "export YARP_ROOT=$PWD/yarp2" >> ~/.profile
echo "export YARP_DIR=$PWD/yarp2/build" >> ~/.profile
source ~/.profile
\endverbatim

 2) Through ~/.bashrc (parsed inside each terminal). For this other option, type:
 
\verbatim
echo "export YARP_ROOT=$PWD/yarp2" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "export YARP_DIR=$PWD/yarp2/build" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
\endverbatim

<br><hr>

This page can be edited at $ASIBOT_ROOT/main/doc/install_yarp_on_ubuntu.dox.

*
*/

